mxCell.value: This constrains Node 0 to the cabin air temperature as a boundary in this network for conducting heat between the air and the shell. Send the cabin air T from the fluid model to this link’s mSourcePressure term, and its mFlux term is the total heat flux pulled from the cabin air, sent back to the fluid model.
Thermal capacitances are the mass times specific heat of aluminum (900 J/kg/K)
Send heater power from the electrical model to these link’s mPowerElectrical term.
Small conductance values for insulation between inner shell and outer optical layer.
Heat convection between shell and air is simplified with these conductors.
Creates the boundary node for emission to space, constrained to the effective temperature of the visible environment.
Emission conductance is area * emissivity * Stefan Boltzmann constant.
We’re using the absorption link’s slot 0 for solar, and slot 1 for lunar infrared.
